    <title type="html"><![CDATA[NTFS Driver for Mac OS]]></title>
    <link href="http://parasnarang.github.io/blog/blog/2013/01/15/ntfs-driver-for-mac-os/"/>
    <updated>2013-01-15T23:16:00+05:30</updated>
    <id>http://parasnarang.github.io/blog/blog/2013/01/15/ntfs-driver-for-mac-os</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<div class='post'>
<div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on">Not being able to copy files to NTFS format external media drives (harddisk, pendrive etc.) is a common issue in Mac OS X.<br /><br />To fix this, an NTFS driver for Mac is required.<br /><br />A few reliable ones are :<br /><br /><ol style="text-align: left;"><li><a href="http://www.paragon-software.com/home/ntfs-mac/download.html" target="_blank">Paragon NTFS Driver</a> : To use this driver for copying files to a Seagate external portable drive, Download this driver for free from the Seagate website <a href="http://www.paragon-software.com/home/ntfs-mac/download.html" target="_blank">here</a>.</li><li><a href="http://www.tuxera.com/community/ntfs-3g-download/" target="_blank">NTFS-3G for Mac</a> : Download it <a href="http://download.cnet.com/NTFS-3G/3000-2094_4-10913782.html" target="_blank">here</a>.</li></ol></div></div>

]]></content>
