    <title type="html"><![CDATA[Eclipse and Tomcat on Mac OS X]]></title>
    <link href="http://parasnarang.github.io/blog/blog/2012/07/23/eclipse-and-tomcat-on-mac-os-x/"/>
    <updated>2012-07-23T22:29:00+05:30</updated>
    <id>http://parasnarang.github.io/blog/blog/2012/07/23/eclipse-and-tomcat-on-mac-os-x</id>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<div class='post'>
<div dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;" trbidi="on"><div style="text-align: left;"><span style="background-color: white; text-align: left;">There is a lot of confusion. Follow these steps. Avoid the pain.</span></div><ol style="text-align: left;"><li><a href="http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/" style="background-color: white;" target="_blank">Download</a><span style="background-color: white;"> Eclipse IDE for Java EE Developers. Uncompress in a folder of your choice.<br /></span></li><li><a href="http://tomcat.apache.org/download-70.cgi" style="background-color: white;" target="_blank">Download</a><span style="background-color: white;"> Tomcat.&nbsp;</span><span style="background-color: white;">Uncompress in a folder of your choice.<br /></span></li><li><span style="background-color: white;"><a href="http://www.eclipsetotale.com/tomcatPlugin.html" target="_blank">Download</a>&nbsp;</span><span style="background-color: white;">Sysdeo Eclipse Tomcat Launcher plugin.<br /></span></li><li><span style="background-color: white;">Unzip the above plugin</span><span style="background-color: white;">&nbsp;in :</span></li><br /><div style="text-align: left;"></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"></div><ul style="text-align: left;"><li><span style="background-color: white;">Eclipse_Home/dropins for Eclipse 3.4, 3.5 and 3.6</span></li><li><span style="background-color: white;">Eclipse_Home/plugins for Eclipse 2.1, 3.0, 3.1, 3.2 and 3.3</span></li></ul><br /><span style="background-color: white;"><li><span style="background-color: white;">Launch Eclipse by double clicking the icon in the folder you had uncompressed to. You must see the Tomcat icons in the toolbar.<br /></span></li><span style="background-color: white;"></span><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-eI77-249RxA/UA14V1eTG9I/AAAAAAAABGE/U5qyqxnaxrU/s1600/Screen+Shot+2012-07-23+at+9.41.46+PM.png" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em; text-align: center;"><img border="0" src="http://2.bp.blogspot.com/-eI77-249RxA/UA14V1eTG9I/AAAAAAAABGE/U5qyqxnaxrU/s1600/Screen+Shot+2012-07-23+at+9.41.46+PM.png" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: left;"></div><li>Set Tomcat version and Tomcat home : Workbench -&gt; Preferences, select Tomcat and set Tomcat version and Tomcat home<br /></li></span><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-JC_b173Wrko/UA14W6VNHTI/AAAAAAAABGM/CT-If_o9-Tw/s1600/Screen+Shot+2012-07-23+at+9.43.04+PM.png" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/-JC_b173Wrko/UA14W6VNHTI/AAAAAAAABGM/CT-If_o9-Tw/s1600/Screen+Shot+2012-07-23+at+9.43.04+PM.png" /></a></div><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><br /></div><li>Now place your project in apache-tomcat-x.x.x/webapps/<br /></li><li>Start Tomcat from Eclipse.<br /></li><li>Visit localhost:8080 from your browser to check if it works.<br /></li></ol>That is it !<br />If you don't want to use this plugin, another way to configure eclipse and tomcat can be found <a href="http://www.banym.de/eclipse/install-tomcat-with-eclipse" target="_blank">here</a>.<ol style="text-align: left;"></ol></div></div>

]]></content>
